The paper deals with error correction coding in the analog context, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the use of metrics and optimization techniques, which are common in signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the evaluation of existing codes, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or machine learning (cs.LG) if the codes are used in those contexts.
